   Feature: Look up the definition of a word
   
  Scenario: Welcome to Wikipedia
       When I am on the wikipedia page
       Then the url will be "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page"
        And the search field can be located by name "search"
        And I wait 2 seconds
        
  Scenario: Define step 2 page element locators
       When I am on the evidence page
       Then the evidence title can be located by id "firstHeading"
       

@StepDef
Given five types of evidence will be shown
 Then the personal experience link can be located by xpath //*[@id="mw-content-text"]/ul[1]/*/a[@title="Personal experience"]
  And the scientific evidence link can be located by xpath //*[@id="mw-content-text"]/ul[1]/li[2]/a
  And the testimonial link can be located by xpath //*[@id="mw-content-text"]/ul[1]/li[3]/a
  And the physical evidence link can be located by xpath //*[@id="mw-content-text"]/ul[1]/li[4]/a
  And the trace evidence link can be located by xpath //*[@id="mw-content-text"]/ul[1]/li[2]/a
  
   
@StepDef
Scenario: the user does not know the definition of evidence
Given I navigate to the wikipedia page  
 When I enter "evidence" into the search field
 Then five types of evidence will be shown 
             